descriptionNullable:
A collection of chest X-rays classified into 9 different categories according to their most relevant characteristics, namely:
Normal, Inflammatory processes (pneumonia), Higher density (pleural effusion, atelectatic consolidation, hydrothorax, empyema), Lower density (pneumotorax, pneumomediastinum, pneumoperitoneum), Obstructive pulmonary diseases (emphysema, bronchopneumonia, bronchiectasis, embolism), Degenerative infectious diseases (tuberculosis , sarcoidosis, proteinosis, fibrosis), Encapsulated lesions (abscesses, nodules, cysts, tumor masses, metastases), Mediastinal changes (pericarditis, arteriovenous malformations, lymph node enlargement) and Chest changes (atelectasis, malformations, agenesis, hypoplasia).
Synthetically augmented database.
Images without any type of patient information, reported by radiologists and provided for study purposes.
